{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": 1,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "After these things the Lord appointed other seventy also, and sent them two and two before his face into every city and place, whither he himself would come."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 2,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Therefore said he unto them,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 17,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the seventy returned again with joy,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Lord, even the devils are subject unto us through thy name.",
          "speaker": "Seventy Disciples"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "The Seventy Return"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 18,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he said unto them,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 21,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "In that hour Jesus rejoiced in spirit, and said,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Jesus Rejoices"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 23,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he turned him unto his disciples, and said privately,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 25,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And, behold, a certain lawyer stood up, and tempted him, saying,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Master, what shall I do to inherit eternal life?",
          "speaker": "Lawyer"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "The Good Samaritan"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 26,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He said unto him,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 27,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Thou shalt love the Lord thy God with all thy heart, and with all thy soul, and with all thy strength, and with all thy mind; and thy neighbour as thyself.",
          "speaker": "Lawyer"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 28,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he said unto him,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 29,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But he, willing to justify himself, said unto Jesus,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "And who is my neighbour?",
          "speaker": "Lawyer"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 30,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And Jesus answering said,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 37,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "He that shewed mercy on him.",
          "speaker": "Lawyer"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then said Jesus unto him,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 38,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Now it came to pass, as they went, that he entered into a certain village: and a certain woman named Martha received him into her house."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Martha and Mary"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 39,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And she had a sister called Mary, which also sat at Jesus' feet, and heard his word."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 40,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But Martha was cumbered about much serving, and came to him, and said,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Lord, dost thou not care that my sister hath left me to serve alone? bid her therefore that she help me.",
          "speaker": "Martha"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 41,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And Jesus answered and said unto her,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    }
  ]
}